It was first developed in 1948 by Walter Frederick Morrison, who called it the " Pluto Platter." The Frisbee brand name is now owned by the Wham-O toy company which started producing the toy in 1955. Frisbees come in a variety of sizes, weights, and designs, each with its own unique flight characteristics. They are typically made of plastic and have a curved edge that allows them to fly through the air with a spinning motion. They can be used for a variety of activities such as casual play, ultimate Frisbee, disc golf, and freestyle. When throwing a Frisbee, it is important to use the correct technique to achieve the desired flight pattern. The most common throwing technique is called a backhand throw, which involves holding the Frisbee with the thumb on top and the fingers on the bottom and flicking the wrist to release the Frisbee. Frisbee is a popular sport and recreational activity for people of all ages. It's also a great way to stay active and improve hand-eye coordination. With the different types of Frisbee sports, it can be enjoyed both individually and in teams.
